Sunny after 5-6 days of rain- breezy.
Cool breeze- air temp. 55- just after a 3 day rain.
Mostly sunny- lt. breeze- day after 100 F temps.
Sorry I missed reporting last week-weather poor.
Surface water temp. 78.6 degrees.  Weather partly cloudy- bright hazy sun.
Crazy weather lately: whitecaps- clouds- rain- thunder + lightning + difficult to get out when sun was high.
Light overcast/bright sun/strong shadows.  Could forest fires out west be affecting sky brightness
Algae evident on windward shores- but not in open areas.  Sky - partly cloudy.
Sky - partly cloudy.  Note: I expect to be out of state until about September 1 - I'll resume then.
Super clear day.  First time since return from Arizona that wind or weather permitted sampling- wind calm.
Lots of rain- very stormy- power out for 6 hours last week.  Many trees down around lake.  Several docks + boat lift overturned.
Clear - no wind- more algae than usual- probably due to the many rainstorms of late.  Many trees down around lake.
Hazy-sunny.  Sunday-nice weekend and lots of boat traffic.
Rain this week totaled about 7 to 8".
We had a total of 12" of rain the past few weeks.  Water appears to be greener than usual.
Very light wind-lots of floating algae in spots.
Partly cloudy- hazy sky. due to forest fires  we've had some very orange sunsets
Clear. thin strato-cirrus  on western horizon
CENTER BASIN - DEEP HOLE-6FT INTEGRATED SAMPLE
sunny clear- clear water- blue clear bright warm day
Hot- minimal wind-lake high due to july rains
Minimal breeze- partial overcast- recent heavy rains- water high
Overcast. Lake heavy with pollen. painted turtle observed and one loon. Eagle earlier in day. Assisted by my wife.
Intermittent overcast. Brightest day of season. Lake quiet. Color grey blue. Loons and 2 eagles spotted this date. Heavy overnight rain.
Bright sun filled day; brightest I have been out this year. Nearly calm waters. Loons and swallows spotted.
Clear- minimal breeze- bright sun- eagle- loons-
Sun with haze- calm and clear. Loons- eagle- belted kingfisher- rose breasted grosbeak- gulls
Beaurtiful- mild day with full sun and small lake chop.
recent heavy rains- hot and humid.Today partial clouds with moderate wind. Eagle and loons and a tern.sediment modewrate in lake from recent rains.
Heavy winds on 6/24/2012 made temperature readings inaccurate because of lack of depth. This portion of study and repeat Secchi was repeated 06/26/2012. Mixed clouds both days.
Clear calm day. Least windy day of year so temp data is most accurate. Clear calm day. Least windy day of year so temp data is most accurate.Assisted by 4 grandchildren- 6 to 11.
Bright buy hazy partial overcast day. Very light chop on waters. Helped by grandchildren to teach them responsible lake behavior and interest. Marne and Delaney Decker and Phoebe Gullingsrud.
Light chop on lake. Loons-swallows. Warm-partial overcast
Hazy- calm day. Eagles- loons-gulls in area. My son Tom assisted.
Overcast with sprinkles- calm winds- juvenile loon seen
Hazy sun- calm-quiet- warm- solitary loon- many gulls- green backed heron
Skies are clear.  Lake level is very high-- highest in ten years.  Twigs- leaves- other detritus on water surface.
Partly cloudy.  Lake level still very high- but lower than it was at the last monitor date-- 6/20/14.
Overcast.  70 degrees F.  Water levels slightly low.
Partly cloudy. 57 degrees.   Many loons.  Only one boat on the lake all day.
Beautiful day.  Sunny and clear. Calm.
Partly cloudy-  winds out of the North East at 12 MPH.  Lots of boat traffic.
Cloudy day- windy.  Several loons.  Eagle fishing.
Partly cloudy.  Thunderstorms to the East.  Patches of algae visible in and on the water.
Mostly sunny.  Windy.  Not much boat traffic.
Light winds out of the South.  Ice off twelve days ago.
Partly cloudy- 65 degrees.  Juvenile eagles soaring above the lake.   Six loons diving.  Only one other boat on the water all afternoon.
Breezy- clear- beautiful day to be on the lake. Breezy- clear- beautiful day to be on the lake.  Abundant pollen in the air and on the surface of the water.

Mostly clear with a few wispy clouds- light breeze.  As we began testing- a loon was swimming and diving across the lake by the entrance to Dark Lake.  A little later another landed nearby.  Camp Manitou campers out kayaking- canoeing and sailing.  Not much other boat traffic.
Cloudy- occasional rain showers- 66 degrees F.
Two eagles soaring above us.  Boat pulling two tubers circling.  Mostly clear and breezy.
Clear- sunny- windy.  Water surface is choppy.  Sun shine glinting on the waves.  Chilly (58.4 degrees F).  Juvenile eagle circling.  Loon fishing nearby.
Sunny- very few clouds.  Light breeze.  Loons calling and flying.
pH probe not working pH probe not working. DO probe stopped working.
pH probe not working. DO probe was replaced and is now working.
